'''Muonium chloride''' is an [[inorganic compound]] composed of [[exotic atom|exotic]] [[muonium]] atoms and is a [[chloride]] (halide) [[chemical formula]] of MuCl. In 2001, scientists successfully synthesized muonium chloride. <ref name="iupac">[http://www.iupac.org/publications/pac/2001/pdf/7302x0377.pdf Names for muonium and hydrogen atoms and their ions] iupac.org ([[Portable Document Format|PDF]])</ref>

== Chemical properties == 
Muonium chloride can dissociate into [[chloride ions]] and positive [[muon]]s.<ref name="MuCl">[http://www.iupac.org/publications/pac/2001/pdf/7302x0377.pdf MuCl is named “muonium chloride”, which yields positive muons (or muonium ions), Mu+, and chloride ions, Cl–, upon dissociation] ([[Portable Document Format|PDF]])</ref>

